This paper deals with integer constraints and algorithms for their manipulation, which are topics that are relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. However, the focus on constraints and their closure suggests that the paper is most likely to belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) category. Other possible categories include Programming Languages (cs.PL), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL), as these fields also deal with constraint manipulation and analysis.
